gomodel:SYNGO_4811  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Figure 3a,b: HA-tagged InSyn2 was coexpressed in primary neuronal cells from mouse hippocampus with GPHN.FingR-GFP, a recombinant protein sensor of endogenous gephyrin (GPHN, a marker for inhibitory synapses) fused to green fluorescent protein (GFP). co-localization was ~50%.\n\nFigure 3d: InSyn2 coimmunoprecipitates with gephyrin (GPHN) when coexpressed in human embryonic kidney 293 (HEK293) cells.. Experimental description: M&M: \"Primary neuronal cultures from mouse hippocampus were prepared as described previously\"\n\nM&M: \"HA-InSyn2 (NM_001143802)\" -->> confirms selected uniprot record" ;
